00:00:03.000 --> 00:00:08.000
 How to optimize picture settings - Perfect for movies and TV series - 

00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:14.000
 All recent TVs have their own picture settings. 

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:21.000
 Sony BRAVIA TV lets you watch movies and TV series with the best quality without manual adjustments. 

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:28.000
 How to set the image mode "Cinema pro" 

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:36.000
 Click the Actions menu, and under Display and Sound settings, look for Photo setup, and set up the image. 

00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:41.000
 * The actual list depends on the country / region, the type of content displayed, and the model of the TV. 

00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:49.000
 Under Picture mode, select "Cinema pro", which will automatically change the picture settings for movies and TV series automatically. 

00:00:57.000 --> 00:01:03.000
 "Cinema pro" is designed in consultation with Sony Pictures' Colorworks to reflect what film directors want on television. 

00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:09.000
 How to adjust the picture settings manually 

00:01:11.000 --> 00:01:17.000
 Click the Actions menu, and under Display and Sound Settings, find the setting Picture, and adjust the image. 

00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:23.000
 * The actual list depends on the country / region, the type of content displayed, and the model of the TV. 

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:28.000
 Under Picture mode, you'll find basic settings like "Brightness" or "Color." 

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:34.000
 The Advanced settings option will allow you to access the details of the image settings. 

00:01:37.000 --> 00:01:41.000
 Image mode overview 

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:52.000
 Android TV 13 models have image mode, each suitable for your content. * The "HDR-Video" mode (HDR video) depends on the model. 

00:01:54.000 --> 00:02:03.000
 Enjoy what you see best. 

